# Translation Standards (Mobile — react-i18next)

## Core Rule

**NEVER hardcode user-facing strings in JSX.** All visible text must come from translation keys.

## Usage

```typescript
import { useTranslations } from '../../hooks';

const FeatureScreen = () => {
  const t = useTranslations('feature');
  const tc = useTranslations('common');

  return (
    <ScreenLayout title={t('title')} description={t('description')}>
      <PrimaryButton text={t('addButton')} />
      <EmptyState message={t('emptyStateNoItems')} isDark={isDark} />
      <SecondaryButton text={tc('cancel')} />
    </ScreenLayout>
  );
};
```

## Namespace Files

Per-feature namespace files, one per locale: `i18n/locales/<locale>/<namespace>.json`

Register each namespace in `i18n/index.ts` — add to `resources.en`, `resources.sr`, `resources.es`, and the `ns` array.

## Key Naming

- camelCase: `addButton`, `emptyStateNoItems`
- Nested for groups: `form.titleLabel`
- **Keys must mirror the web app's `messages/en.json`** exactly for shared features

```json
{
  "title": "Feature",
  "addButton": "+ Add Item",
  "emptyStateNoItems": "No items yet.",
  "form": {
    "titleLabel": "Title",
    "descriptionLabel": "Description"
  }
}
```

## Interpolation

Use `{{variable}}` syntax — double braces (differs from web's single braces):

```json
{ "deleteMessage": "Delete \"{{title}}\"?" }
```

```typescript
t('deleteMessage', { title: item.title });
```

## Critical: Add Keys to All Locales Simultaneously

Every new key must go into `en`, `sr`, AND `es` locale files at the same time. Missing keys fall back to English silently.

## New Feature Checklist

1. Create `i18n/locales/en/<feature>.json`, `sr/<feature>.json`, `es/<feature>.json`
2. Register namespace in `i18n/index.ts`
3. Include at minimum: `title`, `description`, `addButton`, `emptyStateNoItems`
4. Put form labels under a `form` nested object

## Incremental Adoption

When you **touch a file**, convert its hardcoded strings to translation keys at the same time. New code must use `useTranslations` from day one.
